
Overview of noun connexion

The noun connexion has 6 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                    
1. connection, connexion, link -- (a connecting shape)
2. connection, connexion, connectedness -- (a relation between things or events (as in the case of one causing the other or sharing features with it); "there was a connection between eating that pickle and having that nightmare")
3. association, connection, connexion -- (the process of bringing ideas or events together in memory or imagination; "conditioning is a form of learning by association")
4. connection, connexion, connector, connecter, connective -- (an instrumentality that connects; "he soldered the connection"; "he didn't have the right connector between the amplifier and the speakers")
5. connection, connexion -- (shifting from one form of transportation to another; "the plane was late and he missed his connection in Atlanta")
6. joining, connection, connexion -- (the act of bringing two things into contact (especially for communication); "the joining of hands around the table"; "there was a connection via the internet")
